3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes two methods to enumerate the size of skip-sliding window codes, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the application of skip-sliding window codes in digital communication and storage systems, which can be related to social and information networks. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper mentions the refinement of enumeration methods to reduce complexity, which can be related to computational complexity.
